Here's the three pieces you need:

### 1. Read the current system theme

```csharp
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified
```

### 2. Subscribe to real-time changes

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs or any page
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");

    // Update UI on the main thread
    MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
    {
        // e.g. swap colors, icons, etc.
    });
};
```

### 3. Force a specific theme (user override)

```csharp
// Lock to dark mode regardless of system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

### Putting it together ‚Äî a settings page example

```csharp
public partial class SettingsPage : ContentPage
{
    public SettingsPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Show current theme on load
        UpdateThemeLabel(Application.Current.RequestedTheme);

        // React to OS-level changes in real time
        Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    private void OnThemeChanged(object sender, AppThemeChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"System theme changed ‚Üí {e.RequestedTheme}");
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() => UpdateThemeLabel(e.RequestedTheme));
    }

    private void UpdateThemeLabel(AppTheme theme)
    {
        ThemeLabel.Text = $"Current theme: {theme}";
    }

    // Picker or toggle callback
    private void OnThemeSelected(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = themePicker.SelectedIndex switch
        {
            0 => AppTheme.Unspecified, // "Follow system"
            1 => AppTheme.Light,
            2 => AppTheme.Dark,
            _ => AppTheme.Unspecified
        };
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `RequestedTheme` ‚Äî read-only, reflects the OS setting.
- `RequestedThemeChanged` ‚Äî fires when the OS theme toggles.
- `UserAppTheme` ‚Äî read/write; set it to override, set to `Unspecified` to follow the system again.
- XAML `AppThemeBinding` (e.g. `{AppThemeBinding Light=White, Dark=Black}`) automatically reacts to both system and `UserAppTheme` changes with no extra code.
